#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Samādhivagga"
msgstr "1. Immersion"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Dutiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇasutta"
msgstr "6. Ascetics and Brahmins (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.6:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsesuṃ, sabbe te cattāri ariyasaccāni yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsesuṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, whatever ascetics and brahmins—past,"

msgctxt "sn56.6:1.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsessanti, sabbe te cattāri ariyasaccāni yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsessanti."
msgstr "future,"

msgctxt "sn56.6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsenti, sabbe te cattāri ariyasaccāni yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsenti."
msgstr ""
"or present—reveal that they are awakened, all of them reveal that they truly "
"awakened to the four noble truths."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.6:2.1"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.6:2.2"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. …"

msgctxt "sn56.6:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā yathābhūtaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ pakāsesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.6:2.4"
msgid "pakāsessanti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn56.6:2.5"
msgid ""
"pakāsenti, sabbe te imāni cattāri ariyasaccāni yathābhūtaṃ abhisambuddhaṃ "
"pakāsenti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.6:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.6:3.2"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
